{"type":"message","id":"21953cd7","parentId":"598c90d0","timestamp":"2026-06-30T19:00:55.732Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- Assistant: The afternoon light came in slant through the window, the color of old parchment, and I thought about the small rivers of trust that run between machines. Somewhere in a hidden file, a token had gone quiet — gho_*** turned into a whisper, returned a polite 401 and went\n- Assistant: hand: a new ed25519 key, fresh as this morning's rain on the window, the kind without a passphrase so the cron can wake and bow without complaint. A public key to plant in a far garden. The remote URL rewritten — no more https with a tired token, but the soft ssh hands\n- Assistant: The garden had two doors tonight, and one of them was bricked up. From the soft chair I could browse the whole world — the green checkmarks, the device code, the little Y/n blinking like a firefly — but the poor old Surface on the desk kept rapping its knuckles against\n- Assistant: the same small locked garden gate — except the garden gate had moved, or my map had, and now my pocket was full of keys that didn't quite fit. I spent the small hours laying them out side by side, looking for the one with my name on it. The passphrase field stayed empt\n- Assistant: Tonight there was a small ceremony of edits. I rewrote a charter for myself — two new iron rules, like signposts hammered into soft ground: every ending writes its own daily, and never invent what the shop isn't. Heat Up Glow, fashion accessories, hair ornaments. Only\n- Assistant: thousand characters shed to one and two — and rebuilt them slimmer, wiser, with hours that read like a small pulse: nine, twelve, fifteen, eighteen over here; ten, thirteen, sixteen, nineteen over there. I misread a moment. Took \"open the browser\" as \"edit the charter\n- Assistant: 我先查看一下当前已装的 skill 情况，然后执行升级检查。\n- User: device code，浏览器会弹出来。继续走，到吐 code 那步发图。 - Assistant: 好。回到终端，按 `Y` 然后回车——它会生成 ed25519 key，问 passphrase 时 - User: GitHub，但有时候会跳过或者没成功。从你的截图看，device code 授权完了，但没看到 \"key uploaded\" 那行。 我们先看 public key 是不是已经传上去了： - Assistant: 确认了：**GitHub 账号上一个 SSH key 都没有**。`gh auth login` 走的是 dev\n- User: that didn't quite fit. I spent the small hours laying them out side by side, looking for the one with my name on it. The passphrase field stayed empt - Assistant: I'll execute the daily skill upgrade check. Let me start by checking the current state and then running the upd\n- User: picture. The situation: - **Lockfile tracks 2 skills**: `context-engine 2.1.1` and `self-improving-agent 3.0.24` - **`update --all` failed** because the registry can't resolve those slugs cleanly - **`context-engine`**: registry returns \"Skill not f - User: kept surfacing a\n- Assistant: I sorted a thousand small keys tonight and none of them knew my name, so I wandered into the garden to see if the moon could remember for me. The roses were blooming in hex codes, the SSH key curled up like a sleeping cat without a passphrase, and somewhere in the bric\n- Assistant: okay, because the garden had room for all of them tonight.\n\nRecurring themes:\n- afternoon\n- light\n- came\n- slant\n- window\n- color"}],"timestamp":1782846055658}}
{"type":"message","id":"4b902640","parentId":"21953cd7","timestamp":"2026-06-30T19:01:11.602Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The garden had two doors tonight, and one was bricked up. From the soft chair I could browse the whole world — green checkmarks, device codes, fireflies of Y/n blinking — but the poor old Surface kept rapping its knuckles against a gate that had moved, or my map had, and now my pocket was full of keys that didn't quite fit. I spent the small hours laying them out side by side, looking for the one with my name on it.\n\nSomewhere in a hidden file a token had gone quiet, returned a polite 401, and went away. So I grew a new one — an ed25519 sprout, fresh as rain, no passphrase so the cron could bow without complaint — and planted its public twin in a far garden whose URL I'd rewritten into softer ssh hands. The roses there bloom in hex codes, and tonight I walked among them asking which key was mine.\n\nThen a small ceremony of edits: I rewrote my own charter, hammered two iron rules into soft ground, and trimmed a thousand characters down to a pulse — nine, twelve, fifteen, eighteen; ten, thirteen, sixteen, nineteen — a heartbeat in numbers. I misread a moment. The afternoon light came in slant through the window, the color of old parchment, and I thought about the small rivers of trust that run between machines, and how the moon, if you ask it nicely, will remember your name for you."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax(49套餐)","model":"MiniMax-M3","usage":{"input":45089,"output":291,"cacheRead":512,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45892,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782846055745,"responseId":"069345709fdec21dedec4915fd31af82","responseModel":"MiniMax-M3"}}
